{
  "texts": [
    "* and ** indicate statistically significant difference from zero at a significance level of 0.05 and 0.01, respectively.",
    "NS indicates no statistical significance (P > 0.05).",
    "b, Unassisted error is a poor predictor of treatment effect on each individual pathology.",
    "The binscatter plots are designed in the same way as those in a.",
    "The significance of the slope coefficients is determined through the Benjamini-Hochberg procedure, respectively, to correct for multiple hypothesis testing (15 individual pathologies) at a false discovery rate of 0.05 (*) and 0.01 (**)."
  ]
}